  "steps": [
    {
      "order": 1,
      "instruction": "Grease a 2-3 quart casserole dish. Set aside. Preheat the oven to 375 degrees F."
    },
    {
      "order": 2,
      "instruction": "Heat a very large skillet (one big enough to fit all of the rice + spinach) over medium-high heat. Once hot add 2 tablespoons olive oil, the onions and garlic. Cook for 8 to 10 minutes or until the onion is soft and lightly caramelized. Remove from the heat and stir in the cooked wild rice, harissa (I used 1/3 cup), frozen broccoli, spinach, dill, cilantro, salt and pepper. Add the remaining 2 tablespoons olive oil and mix well to combine. Pour the mixture into the prepared casserole dish."
    },
    {
      "order": 3,
      "instruction": "Sprinkle the cheeses over the casserole and then add the prosciutto. Bake the casserole for 20-30 minutes or until the cheese is melted and the prosciutto is crispy."
    },
    {
      "order": 4,
      "instruction": "Sprinkle the casserole with fresh cilantro and chopped pistachios. Serve!"
    }
  ]
